MY FRIEND MONTAG<br>
<br>
I couldn’t help myself.  West Karana was just too tempting.  It was daytime.  The werewolf would only come out at night, right?  I followed the road east and found guards from Qeynos.  Hey, it was just like home!  I even killed a cougar or two with the guards not too far away.  Success breeds bravery… and stupidity.<br>
<br>
Able to track, I knew what could kill me and in what direction it would come from.  I was smart, I understood loc’s, and I was stealthy.  On the track:  Ogres.  What did ogres look like anyway?  Time to find out!<br>
<br>
I crept through the forest, avoiding ANYTHING and everything.  Keep in mind, I was probably around or less than my tenth season.  From a hilltop location, got a nice view of the ogres.  Ugly!  <br>
<br>
Fate: tempted.  Mission: accomplished.  <br>
<br>
It was time to head back home.  I had barely made any progress when I was ambushed.  By a lion, no less!  I thought animals were supposed to LIKE me.  I stood my ground, lions were no big deal…  At least they weren't supposed to.  This lion was stronger.  Funny, for such a big kitty, you’d think I’d have better luck hitting it!  Well, I had wanted to go home… my wish was granted.  Welcome to Qeynos, naked boy!<br>
<br>
Darkness was falling fast, and I booked it to West Karana.  I had an approximate loc for my body, and likewise knew where it was in reference to the Ogres.  I just had to be more careful this time.  I reached the ogres and where the lion had killed me.  No corpse.  IMPOSSIBLE!  I shouted for help.<br>
        “Anybody seen my corpse?”<br>
<br>
So, this guy showed up.  I have no idea where he came from or why he was so off the beaten path.  His name was Montag, a sturdy looking paladin.  He volunteered to help.  <br>
<br>
We met on a corpse run… it was the first of many.<br>
<br>
Montag and I were immediate friends.  Indeed, he was my first, only, and BEST buddy in Norrath.  Though I’m not sure, I think he felt the same because we were pretty much inseparable.  Duoing in Blackburrow, dying in the Qeynos catacombs, journeying to Everfrost… everything was easier and funner with Montag around.  With my snare and his heals, we were one fantastic fighting force!<br>
<br>
And memories?  You better believe it!  Like the time we survived a journey all the way to North Karana, only for me to be killed by a griffin near the gypsies.  If I recall, Montag died as well, trying to drag me.  Like the time we fought Mammoth calves in Everfrost with a new Ranger friend named Calliak.  Like the time I was approached in Blackburrow by an Erudite Necromancer named Armic.  He gave me 100 plat.  It was the most money I’d ever seen in my life.  I was stunned and immediately gave half of it to Montag.  <br>
<br>
“Wow, where’d you get that?!” he whispered.<br>
“This guy just gave it to me!”<br>
<br>
Armic took us underwater and up a ladder where, with his help, we defeated the giant snakes up on the platform.  Wow, Necromancers are really something!  <br>
<br>
